Contract
Standard / Permanent


Location
GB-ENG-London




Job function
FINANCIAL AND TECHNICAL EXPERTISE


Reference
PS&000001






Apply


Derivatives Execution & Clearing (DEC) encompasses listed derivatives execution agency, OTC clearing, listed derivatives clearing and commodity futures. DEC is one pillar of the Prime Solutions and Financing (PS&F) business which includes multi-asset execution, clearing, prime-brokerage and financing for clients.
 
Candidate will become a member of the DEC Product function reporting to the Head of DEC EMEA Clearing Product. DEC Clearing Product is responsible for the delivery of Clearing House product launches and related services on behalf of BNPP. Candidate will be expected to understand regulation evolution as it impacts DEC and its clients.
 
Key Responsibilities:

Understand, develop and execute on business strategy and priorities

Regulation:  

Keep abreast of the evolving regulatory landscape and how this impacts both DEC and DEC’s clients. 

Advise client facing teams of key updates that will enable them to discuss with clients.

Perform analysis of evolutions of regulatory oversight and manage local product strategy / enhancements / adaptation accordingly: specifically re the impact of EMIR, Basel III, MiFID on the product offering.

Client: 

Supporting client facing teams including Sales and Relationship Management. 

Anticipate and address the market’s needs on an ongoing basis, to create a market-leading solution for our target market segments.

Product training and support on Product Offer for the Sales, Relationship Management and Client Solutions teams, including client engagement as required.

Develop Pitch Book and Product Offering marketing material in co-operation with Marketing and Client Development.

Promote BNP Paribas brand on our key markets and in accordance with our product and solutions strategy. 

Product: 

Sponsor new platform functionality.

Develop product strategy and future roadmap for the growth of the platform, including new service developments, solutions to meet client requirements, ensuring platform meets capacity needs of DEC.

Develop business cases for new platform functionality and enhancements.

Develop pricing models, pricing guidelines for new platform functionality.

Maintain existing services by identifying the required evolution.

CCP: 

Represent BNPP on various CCP Working Groups, Product Committees and Design Authorities.

Maintain excellent working relationships with CCP’s.

Qualifications 
 
Essential Experience 

Proven track record of delivering results on time.

Strong clearing and operational business experience. 

Experience of defining / sponsoring projects across several support functions.

Strong product knowledge - experience working with Listed & OTC derivatives.

In-depth knowledge of clearing lifecycle.

Sound understanding of industry initiatives, particularly around regulations.

Proficient using MS Office (Excel, PowerPoint etc).

Drive for results - Delivers high quality work.

Risk awareness - Demonstrates a good awareness of risk and fundamental risk concepts and always considers risk in his/her daily activities.

Corporate role model, integrity & ethics - Acts with discipline and high ethical standards.

Team player & cross cultural awareness - Works effectively in a team. Collaborates and shares information and solutions with colleagues, with other teams and stakeholders.

Client focus - Sees stakeholders as well as external clients as “customers”.  
Technical competencies

Market, product & business - Is genuinely interested in financial markets and continually learning and staying abreast of new developments. Evidences a good appreciation of economics and market dynamics, with enough understanding to present views on market conditions and trends. 

Business risk - Understands the market, credit, operational, compliance, legal, regulatory and reputational risks of transactions he/she manages. 
Essential personal skills

Diligence - Displays dedication and prioritises problems by considering the impact on the business; identifies quick-wins.

Resilience - Stays calm and positive, controls his/her emotions in conflict or any situation of intense stress (due to market, time or client pressure). 

Communication (Active listener and clear communicator) - Communicates clearly too all stakeholders and clients. Communicates pro-actively with management, escalating issues as necessary.

Innovation - Thinks laterally to identify other sources of useful information and sees ways around obstacles and barriers. 


Apply















